<usermanual>
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

								* Choice Reaction Time Task (Touchscreen)*
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 08-17-2018
last updated:  04-16-2024 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 04-16-2024 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
This script implements a Choice Reaction Time Task for the touchscreen.
 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
TASK DESCRIPTION
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
Choice Reaction Time Task: press a home button that is presented within the half circle of 5 possible
response buttons until one of the response buttons turns yellow, then click the yellow response button 
as fast as possible

The Choice Reaction Time Task tracks the durations participants spent on various subtasks:
1. time spent on HomeButton
2. time between onset of target stimulus and lifting finger off HomeButton (A)
3. time between lifting finger off HomeButton and pressing down on target stimulus (B)
4. time spent on target stimulus (C)
5. time between lifting finger off target stimulus and pressing down on HomeButton (D)

Note: 
The stimuli in this script can be sized absolutely so that distances btw. buttons are the same
on each monitor. To do so, go to section Editable Parameters and check out parameters.runAbsoluteSizes
and parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm.

By default, this script uses proportional sizing; using 100% of the available screen height and
screen width = 4/3 * screen height (width:height: 4:3)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 2 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'choicereactiontimetask_touchscreen_raw*.iqdat'

build:							The specific Inquisit version used (the 'build') that was run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
date, time: 					date and time script was run 
subject, group: 				with the current subject/groupnumber
session:						with the current session id

blockcode, blocknum:			the name and number of the current block (built-in Inquisit variable)
trialcode, trialnum: 			the name and number of the currently recorded trial (built-in Inquisit variable)
									Note: trialnum is a built-in Inquisit variable; it counts all trials run; even those
									that do not store data to the data file such as feedback trials. Thus, trialnum 
									may not reflect the number of main trials run per block. 
										
(parameter) runAbsoluteSizes:	true (1) = runs absolutely sized canvas (see (parameter) canvasHeight_in_mm)
								false (0) = uses proportionally sized canvas (uses width = 4/3*screenHeight) (default)

(parameter) canvasHeight_in_mm:	!!!only relevant if (parameter) runAbsoluteSizes = true (1)		
								The height of the active canvas in mm (default: 140mm ~ ipad screen height)
								=> the width of the active canvas size is automatically set at 4/3*canvasHeight
								=> all other stimuli are sized proportionally for the active canvas size
								=> Result: you achieve the same sized stimuli on all screens
								=> IF the screen is not sufficient to allow for the canvassize
								the script will terminate prematurely.										
										
										
list.practiceCorrect.mean:		stores the proportion correct of the last 5 responses during the current practice session

practicePass:					0 = participant did not pass practice criteria; 
								1 = participant passed practice criteria	

	
trialcount:						counts all trials (trial = current trial sequence) in a block
isi:							current interstimulus interval in ms
targetPosition:					response square 1-5
responseArea:					stores the response area clicked
								choice Reaction Time Task: 'target button' vs. 'elsewhere'  vs. " " (did not respond during response window)
																		
ACC:							1=correct/right stimulus, 
								2="elsewhere" i.e. outside the stimulus; 
								3 = no response
									
finalACC:						stores final correctness of response (1 = correct; 0 = incorrect)
								choice Reaction Time Task: correct = target is pressed
									
rt:								response time (in ms) from onset of Stim until the stim is pressed
								(rt is empty if the stim is not pressed)
									
rt_down1:						script.elapsedTime (in ms) of clicking home-button (measured relative to start of script in ms)
								!Note: if finger lifts off home button prior to Stim appearance, 
								rt_down1 resets to the moment the finger returns to the home button
								and isi is restarted from that moment.
										
rt_up1:							script.elapsedTime (in ms) of lifting finger off home-button (measured relative to start of script in ms)
								Note: rt_up1 is measured AFTER Stim appearance
										
rt_down2:						script.elapsedTime (in ms) of clicking stim-button or 'elsewhere' (measured relative to start of script in ms)
rt_up2:							script.elapsedTime (in ms) of lifting finger off stim-button or 'elsewhere' (measured relative to start of script in ms)

rt_down3:						script.elapsedTime (in ms) of clicking home-button after lifting finger off stim-button (measured relative to start of script in ms)					
								Note: if participants stays on home button until stim appears 
								rt_down3 is assigned rt_down1 of the next trial

stimPresentTime:				timestamp of target square (measured relative to start of script in ms):
								the time (in ms) measured from start of script until this target appeared on screen
									
A:		time (in ms) btw. onset of target button (stimPresentTime) and lifting finger off home button (rt_up1)
B:		time (in ms) btw taking finger off Home Button and pressing down on Stim Button
C:		time (in ms) finger spends on Stim Button (pressing down on stimulus to lifting off stimulus)
D:		time (in ms) btw taking finger off Stim Button and pressing down again on Home Button
									
duration_HomeButton:		time (in ms) finger spent on HomeButton
count_earlyResponses:		counts premature lift-offs (off homebutton) during the current trial
total_earlyResponses:		counts premature lift-offs (off homebutton) across all test trials

	
(2) Summary data file: 'choicereactiontimetask_touchscreen_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:					Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
(parameter) runAbsoluteSizes:		true (1) = runs absolutely sized canvas (see (parameter) canvasHeight_in_mm)
									false (0) = uses proportionally sized canvas (uses width = 4/3*screenHeight) (default)

(parameter) canvasHeight_in_mm:		!!!only relevant if (parameter) runAbsoluteSizes = true (1)		
									The height of the active canvas in mm (default: 140mm ~ ipad screen height)
									=> the width of the active canvas size is automatically set at 4/3*canvasHeight
									=> all other stimuli are sized proportionally for the active canvas size
									=> Result: you achieve the same sized stimuli on all screens
									=> IF the screen is not sufficient to allow for the canvassize
									the script will terminate prematurely.								
									
choiceRTDuration:					stores the duration (in ms) of the choice RT task (only test session; excludes demo & practice)

practicePass_choiceRT:				0 = participant did not pass practice criteria for choiceRT; 
									1 = participant passed practice criteria for choiceRT
									
meanRT_choiceRT:					mean latency (in ms) of pressing down on stim (latency measured from onset of target to 
									pressing down on it); only correct responses
									
ACC_choiceRT:						mean proportion correct (correct = target square was hit as opposed to elsewhere or no response)

total_earlyResponses_choiceRT:		counts premature lift-offs (off homebutton) across all test trials in the choiceRT task

only for responses with finalACC = 1:
meanDuration_A:				mean duration (in ms) btw. onset of target button (stimPresentTime) and lifting finger off home button
meanDuration_B:				mean duration (in ms) btw taking finger off Home Button and pressing down on Stim Button
meanDuration_C:				mean duration (in ms) finger spent on Stim Button
meanDuration_D:				mean duration (in ms) btw taking finger off Stim Button and pressing down again on Home Button
									
meanDuration_HomeButton:	mean duration (in ms) finger spent on HomeButton

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EXPERIMENTAL SET-UP 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

1. Intro with a demo: runs 2 demo trials for each participant regardless of performance

2. Practice:
- max. 10 trials
- Pass Criteria: 5 correct trials in a row (correct = finger lifts off home button after square appears and presses down on square within 5000ms)

3. Test: 20 trials (default; each response button runs 4 times)
- 4 isi (see list.isi_choiceRT: 1000ms, 3000, 2000ms, 4000ms), selected randomly
	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
provided under section Editable Instructions

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

User Interface:
/runAbsoluteSizes:							true = runs absolutely sized canvas (see parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm)
											false = uses proportionally sized canvas (uses width = 4/3*screenHeight) (default)

/canvasHeight_in_mm:							!!!only relevant if parameters.runAbsoluteSizes = true (1)			
											the height of the active canvas in mm (default: 140mm ~ ipad screen height)
											=> the width of the active canvas size is automatically set at 4/3*canvasHeight
											=> all other stimuli are sized proportionally for the active canvas size
											=> you can further customize the size of the homeButton/responseButtonSize/etc.
											=> Result: you achieve the same sized stimuli on all screens
											=> IF the screen is not sufficient to allow for the canvassize
											the script will terminate prematurely.
											
/homeButtonSize:							the proportional size of the Home Button (relative to canvas) (default: 15%)
/responsebuttonSize::						the proportional size of the response squares (relative to canvas) (default: 15%)																	
											
/HomeButton_choiceRT_y:						the vertical position of the HomeButton in the choice Reaction Time Task in canvas height% (default: 50%)
/circleproportion:							proportion of canvas height used for the circle radius of response buttons in choice Reaction Time Task (default: 0.4)
											
											


/button1_choiceRT:							true (default) = button 1 (left button) is presented; false = button 1 not presented
/button2_choiceRT:							true (default) = button 2 is presented; false = button 2 not presented
/button3_choiceRT:							true (default) = button 3 (center button) is presented; false = button 3 not presented
/button4_choiceRT:							true (default) = button 4 is presented; false = button 4 not presented
/button5_choiceRT:							true (default) = button 5 (right button) is presented; false = button 5 not presented

/numberTestTrials:							the number of test trials run (default: 20)
												Note: needs to be divisible by the number of presented responsebuttons (responseaquares)
												
/presentFinalRTfeedback:					true (1): participants receive feedback about their average (correct) reaction time 
												at test termination (default)
											false (0): no reaction time feedback is provided at the end



/feedback:									presents feedback (default: 2000ms)

/homeButton_RW:								home button response window until a reminder is flashed onto the screen (default:  6000ms)
												Note: the trial continues until the home button is pressed
												
/stim_RW:									response window after stim is presented (default: 6000ms)	

</usermanual>


<parameters>
/runAbsoluteSizes = false
/canvasHeight_in_mm = 140
/homeButtonSize = 15%
/responsebuttonSize = 15%
/HomeButton_choiceRT_y = 50%
/circleproportion = 0.3

/button1_choiceRT = true
/button2_choiceRT = true
/button3_choiceRT = true
/button4_choiceRT = true
/button5_choiceRT = true

/numberTestTrials = 20
/presentFinalRTfeedback = true

/feedback = 2000
/homeButton_RW = 6000
/stim_RW = 6000
</parameters>

<shape canvas>
/shape = rectangle
/color = red
/ size = (expressions.canvasWidth, expressions.canvasHeight)
</shape>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<item choiceRT_intro>
/1 = "~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n
This is a test of how quickly you can touch a YELLOW square on the screen according to the rule:

As soon as you see the YELLOW square, touch it!

After you have touched the YELLOW square, return to the HOME button and wait for the next YELLOW square."
/2 = "~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n
This is a test of how quickly you can touch a YELLOW square on the screen according to the rule:

As soon as you see the YELLOW square, touch it!

After you have touched the YELLOW square, return to the HOME button and wait for the next YELLOW square."

/3 = "Now it’s time for you to practice the task. 

Remember: 
Touch the yellow square as quickly as you can. 

Then return your finger to the HOME button and hold it down until you see the next YELLOW square.


Press the START button when you are ready to begin."

/4 = "Now you will start the real task which is the same as the one you just practiced. It will take approx. 2 minutes.

Remember: 
Touch the YELLOW square as quickly as you can. 

Then return your finger to the HOME button and hold it down until you see the next YELLOW square.

Press the START button when you are ready to begin."
</item>


<item choiceRT_feedback>
/1 = "You did not touch the YELLOW square. Make sure you touch inside the YELLOW square."
/2 = "Keep your finger on the home button until the YELLOW square appears."
/3 = "Remember: touch the YELLOW square."
/4 = "Return your finger to the HOME button."
</item>


<item instructionReminder>
/1 = "Put your finger firmly on the HOME button to begin the task. "
</item>


<text Welcome>
/ items = ("Welcome!")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 8%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 20%)
/ size = (80%, 10%)
/ vjustify = center
/ erase = false
</text>

<text header>
/ items = ("This is a reaction time task for the touchscreen.")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 4%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 35%)
/ size = (80%, 10%)
/ vjustify = center
/ erase = false
</text>

<text introInstructions>
/ items = ("Touch the HOME button now for a demonstration")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 4%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 90%)
/ size = (80%, 10%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

<button showHB>
/ caption = "Touch here to show the HOME Button"
/ size = (40%, 5%)
/ position = (50%, 95%)
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</button>

<text demoStimReminder>
/ items = ("As soon as you see the YELLOW square, touch it as quickly as you can!")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 5%)
/ size = (80%, 10%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

<button choiceRT_continue>
/ caption = "START"
/ size = (30%, 8%)
/ position = (50%, 90%)
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</button>


<text finish>
/ items = ("Thank you!")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 8%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 40%)
/ size = (80%, 80%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

<text finalFeedback>
/ items = ("<%expressions.finalFeedback%>")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 4%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 60%)
/ size = (80%, 20%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

<expressions>
/finalFeedback = if (parameters.presentFinalRTfeedback == true){
	if (values.practicePass == 1){
"You hit the YELLOW square in <%expressions.ACC_choiceRT*100%>% of all trials
Your average reaction time was: <%expressions.meanRT_choiceRT%> ms"		
	}
} else {
	""
}
</expressions>

<button exit>
/ caption = "Exit"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 90%)
/ size = (30%, 8%)
</button>

<text monitorSizeFail>
/ items = ("This task requires a minimum screen height of <%parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm%> mm.
Your current screen has been evaluated to be too small.")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 4%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (50%, 50%)
/ size = (80%, 20%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE LISTS: change editable lists here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: list.targetbuttons_choiceRT dynamically assembles a list of the active target positions;
samples randomly without replacement (constraint on maxrunsize: 4 samplings of the same position in a row is the maximum);
<list targetbuttons_choiceRT>
/ replace = false
/ maxrunsize = 4
</list>


Note: list.isi_choiceRT randomly (with replacement) selects an isi
<list isi_choiceRT>
/items = (1000, 2000, 3000, 4000)
/ replace = true
</list>

Note: list.isi_choiceRT randomly selects an isi
<list isi_choiceRTpractice>
/items = (1000, 2000, 3000, 4000)
/ replace = true
</list>


**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/ canvassize = (expressions.canvasWidth, expressions.canvasHeight)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = (166, 166, 166)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ inputdevice = mouse
/ screencolor = (166, 166, 166)
</defaults>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

***********************
raw data file
***********************

<data>
/ columns = (expressions.targetStimButtonx_px

build, computer.platform, date, time, subject, group, session, blockcode, blocknum, 
trialcode, trialnum, parameters.runAbsoluteSizes, parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm,
list.practiceCorrect.mean, values.practicePass, 
values.trialcount, values.isi,values.targetPosition,
values.responseArea, values.ACC, values.finalACC, 
values.rt, values.rt_down1, values.rt_up1, values.rt_down2, values.rt_up2, values.rt_down3, values.stimPresentTime,
expressions.A, expressions.B, expressions.C, expressions.D,
expressions.duration_HomeButton, 
values.count_earlyResponses, values.total_earlyResponses)
</data>

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, parameters.runAbsoluteSizes, parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm, display.canvasHeight, display.canvasWidth, 

values.choiceRTDuration, 
values.practicePass_choiceRT, 
expressions.meanRT_choiceRT, expressions.ACC_choiceRT,
values.total_earlyResponses_choiceRT
expressions.meanDuration_A,
expressions.meanDuration_B,
expressions.meanDuration_C,
expressions.meanDuration_D,
expressions.meanDuration_HomeButton)
</summarydata>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
                                    
/practice: 				1 = practice session; 0 = test session
/trialcount:			counts all trials (trial = sequence of 2 trials) in a block
/repeat:				0 = new trial sequence; 1 = repeated trialsequence after early response
/isi:					current inter stimulus interval in ms 
/valid:					helper variable to determine valid responses for trial that conclude with lifting finger of target button
/countUP:				counts the number of UP responses in a trial

/targetposition:			
						choice RT task:
								1 = first button (from left)
								...
								5 = last button (from left)
/nr_stims:				stores the number of active response rectangles in choice Reaction Time Task

/button1_choiceRT-
/button5_choiceRT:		true = response rectangle is activated; 0 = response rectangle is deactivated
							Note: response rectangle 'button1' => 12 o'clock position; going clockwise

/selectFeedback:		stores the itemnumber of the current feedback Stim
/choiceRTDuration:		duration (in ms) of test
/stopChoiceRTPractice:	1 = stop practice block (pass criteria has been reached); 0 = otherwise
/practicePass:			1 = practice criteria has been reached; 0 = otherwise

<values>
/practice = 0
/trialcount = 0
/repeat = 0
/isi = 0
/valid = 0

/countUP = 0

/targetPosition = 0
/nr_stims = 0

/selectFeedback = 0

/choiceRTDuration = "not run"
/stopChoiceRTPractice = 0
/practicePass = 1
/practicePass_choiceRT = 1
</values>


/responseArea:				stores the response area clicked 
									choice Reaction Time Task: target button vs. elsewhere
/correct:					0=incorrect/wrong stimulus, 1=correct/right stimulus, 2=”elsewhere” i.e. outside the stimulus				
/finalACC:					stores correctness of response (1 = correct; 0 = incorrect)
									choice Reaction Time Task: correct = target; 0 = otherwise
/rt_down1:					script.elapsedTime (in ms) of clicking home-button (measured relative to start of script in ms)
/rt_up1:					script.elapsedTime (in ms) of lifting finger off home-button
/rt_down2:					script.elapsedTime (in ms) of clicking stim-button
/rt_up2:					script.elapsedTime (in ms) of lifting finger off stim-button 
/rt_releaseHB:				latency (in ms) of lifting finger off home-button After stim presentation (measured from onset of stimulus)

/stimPresentTime:			stores the script.elapsedTime at the current stim presentation time

/prev_stimPresentTime:		stores the stim present Time from the previous trial

/stimButtonOnset:			stores the script elapsed time predicted to present the Stim Button for the current trial
/count_earlyResponses:		counts how many times values.rt_down1 was adjusted after premature lift-offs
/countdownresponses:		tracks the number of DOWN responses recorded in critical trials

<values>
/responseArea = ""
/ACC = 0
/finalACC = 0
/rt_down1 = 0
/rt_up1=0
/rt_down2 = 0
/rt_up2=0
/rt_releaseHB = 0
/rt = 0
/rt_down3 = 0
/stimPresentTime = 0
/stimButtonOnset = 0
/count_earlyResponses = 0
/total_earlyResponses = 0
/total_earlyResponses_choiceRT = 0
/countdownresponses = 0
</values>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Expressions to define the active canvas size on the current monitor
/ px_per_mm: 				pixel per mm (conversion rate on the current monitor)

/screenHeight_inmm:			the calculated screen height in mm (based on the available pixels and expressions.px_per_mm)

/canvasHeight_inpx:			calculates the canvasHeight in pixel used for the task on the current monitor
								- takes into account whether absolute sizing is to be used

/canvasWidth_inpx:			calculates the canvasWidth in pixels used for the task on the current monitor
							The width is always 4/3*the height (=> width:height = 4:3)

Expressions that calculate the areas of the stim buttons

/StimButtonx_choiceRT_px-
/targetStimButton_right:		Expressions that calculate the pixel borders for the stim/target response rectangles


Expressions that calculate latency measures
/duration_HomeButton:			time (in ms) finger spends on HomeButton
/A:								time (in ms) btw. onset of stim button (values.stimPresentTime) and lifting finger off home button (values.rt_up1)
/B:								time (in ms) btw taking finger off Home Button and pressing down on Stim Button
/C:								time (in ms) finger spends on Stim Button (pressing down on stimulus to lifting off stimulus)
/D:								time (in ms) btw taking finger off Stim Button and pressing down again on Home Button

/meanRT_choiceRT:				mean latency (in ms) of pressing down on stim (latency measured from onset of stimulus to pressing down on it)
/meanRT_complexRT:				mean latency (in ms) of pressing down on correct stim (latency measured from onset of stimulus to pressing down on it)
/meanRT_choiceRT:				mean latency (in ms) of pressing down on correct stim=target (latency measured from onset of stimulus to pressing down on it)

<expressions>
/ px_per_mm = display.height/display.getmmy(display.height, 1)
/screenHeight_inmm = display.getmmy(display.height)
/canvasHeight = if (parameters.runAbsoluteSizes == true && expressions.screenHeight_inmm >= parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm){
	1mm * parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm;
} else {
	1px * display.height;	
}

/canvasWidth = if (parameters.runAbsoluteSizes == true && expressions.screenHeight_inmm >= parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm){
	1mm * parameters.canvasHeight_in_mm * 4/3;
} else {
	1px * display.height * 4/3;
}

/targetStimButtonx_px = shape.target.hposition
/targetStimButtony_px = shape.target.vposition
/targetStimButton_top = 1px * (expressions.targetStimButtony_px - 0.5 * display.getPixelsY(shape.target.height))
/targetStimButton_bottom = 1px * (expressions.targetStimButtony_px + 0.5 * display.getPixelsY(shape.target.height))
/targetStimButton_left = 1px * (expressions.targetStimButtonx_px - 0.5 * display.getPixelsX(shape.target.width))
/targetStimButton_right = 1px * (expressions.targetStimButtonx_px + 0.5 *  display.getPixelsX(shape.target.width))

/HomeButtonx_px = display.getPixelsX(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.hposition)
/HomeButtony_px = display.getPixelsY(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.vposition)
/HomeButton_top = expressions.HomeButtony_px - 0.5 * display.getPixelsY(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.height)
/HomeButton_bottom = expressions.HomeButtony_px + 0.5 * display.getPixelsY(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.height)
/HomeButton_left = expressions.HomeButtonx_px - 0.5 * display.getPixelsX(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.width)
/HomeButton_right = expressions.HomeButtonx_px + 0.5 * display.getPixelsX(shape.homeButton_choiceRT.width)

/duration_HomeButton = 
if (values.rt_down1 != ""){
	if (values.rt_up1 != ""){
		values.rt_up1-values.rt_down1;
	} else {
		script.elapsedTime - values.rt_down1;
	}		
} else {
	"";
}

/A = if (values.rt_up1 != "" && values.stimPresentTime != ""){
	values.rt_up1 - values.stimPresentTime;
} else {
	"";
}

/B = if (values.rt_down2 != "" && values.rt_up1 != ""){
	values.rt_down2 - values.rt_up1;
} else {
	"";
}

/C = if (values.rt_up2 != "" && values.rt_down2 != ""){
	values.rt_up2 - values.rt_down2	
} else {
	"";
}

/D = if (values.rt_down3 != "" && values.rt_up2 != ""){
	values.rt_down3-values.rt_up2;
} else {
	"";
}

/meanRT_choiceRT = list.latencies_choiceRT.mean
/ACC_choiceRT = list.ACC_choiceRT.mean

/meanDuration_A = list.durationsA.mean
/meanDuration_B = list.durationsB.mean
/meanDuration_C = list.durationsC.mean
/meanDuration_D = list.durationsD.mean

/meanDuration_HomeButton = list.homeButton_durations.mean
</expressions>


3 Circle Coordinates: expressions to calculate 5 circle positions around the center coordinate
with expressions.radius_px

<expressions>
/centerx = 0.5 * display.canvasWidth
/centery = 0.5 * display.canvasHeight

/radius_px = parameters.circleproportion * display.canvasHeight
/Radians_angle45 = rad(45)

/heightchange_angle90 = expressions.radius_px
/widthchange_angle90 = 0 
/heightchange_angle45 = sin(expressions.Radians_angle45) * expressions.radius_px
/widthchange_angle45 = cos(expressions.Radians_angle45) * expressions.radius_px
/heightchange_angle0 = 0
/widthchange_angle0 = expressions.radius_px
</expressions>

